South African Stocks Fall to 14-Week Low, Heading for Worst Week Since May

-- B y   S i k o n a t h i   M a n t s h a n t s h a
-- 
2011-03-11T07:38:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-11/south-african-stocks-fall-to-14-week-low-heading-for-worst-week-since-may.html
  South Africa ’s stocks declined to
the lowest intraday level in 14 weeks, led by BHP Billiton Plc
and Anglo American Plc, and headed for the biggest weekly drop
since May.  The FTSE/JSE Africa All Share Index retreated for a sixth
day, slumping 1.2 percent to 30,523.63 by 9:34 a.m. in
Johannesburg, extending its loss this week to 5.7 percent. BHP,
the world’s biggest mining company, slipped for a fifth day,
losing 1.8 percent to 250.69 rand.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Sikonathi Mantshantsha in Johannesburg at 
